function isBored(string $sentence): int {
    // Split the sentence into individual words using spaces as delimiters.
    $words = explode(' ', $sentence);

    // Initialize a counter to keep track of boredom sentences.
    $boredCount = 0;

    // Iterate through each word in the array.
    foreach ($words as $word) {
        // Check if the current word starts with "I".
        if (strtolower(substr($word, 0, 1)) == 'i') {
            // Increment the boredom counter by one.
            $boredCount++;
        }
    }

    return $boredCount;
}
```

This function takes a string as input and counts the number of sentences that start with "I" or "i". It then returns this count as an integer.

